ce:section.ce:para:
In addition, to check the stability of the structures, we have estimated their respective cohesive energy/atom from Eq. (1). All the GQDs we have chosen are stable, as evident from the negative values of cohesive energy/atom in Table 1. By mere observation, it has been noted that according to the increase in number of carbon atoms (N
C
) of the structures, the cohesive energy value increases (more negative). Here, the least and most stable structures obtained are QD-0 and QD-7 respectively. Among the 8 selected GQDs, all appear to be having a common point group symmetry CS which contains only two symmetry operations i.e. E : the identity operation and σ : the mirror plane. Therefore, we have obtained a class of quantum dots which has horizontal mirror plane of inversion.


We have observed from Fig. 2(a) that the value of the DOS at Fermi level is zero which confirms that the structure shows semi-metallic behavior. A small or large HOMO-LUMO gap represent soft or hard molecule respectively in terms of chemical hardness (
   η
). This chemical parameter implies the resistance to the distortion of the electron cloud of a chemical under the presence of small perturbation during a synthesis process. The electronegativity (
   χ
), chemical potential (
   μ
) and chemical hardness (
   η
) evaluated [57] for all the structures using Eq. (3) are presented in Table 3.
